2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- rajaniemi.freenode.net Message of the Day - 
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- Welcome to rajaniemi.freenode.net in Helsinki, Finland.  Our thanks to
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- Aalto University for sponsoring this server!
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	-  
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- RAJANIEMI, Hannu  (1978-). Born in Ylivieska, Finland, Rajaniemi is the
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- author of two novels and several short stories, and his debut novel 'The
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- Quantum Thief' was nominated for the 2011 Locus Award for Best First
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- Novel.  Rajaniemi lives in Edinburgh, Scotland where he is founding
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- director of ThinkTank Maths, a commercial research organisation.
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	-  
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	-  
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- Welcome to freenode - supporting the free and open source
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- software communities since 1998.
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	-  
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- By connecting to freenode you indicate that you have read and
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- accept our policies and guidelines as set out on https://freenode.net
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	-  
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- In the event that you observe behaviour that contravenes our policies,
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- please notify a volunteer staff member via private message, or send us an
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- e-mail to complaints@freenode.net -- we will do our best to address the
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- situation within a reasonable period of time, and we may request further
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- information or, as appropriate, involve other parties such as channel operators 
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- Group Contacts representing an on-topic group.
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	-  
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- freenode runs an open proxy scanner.
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	-  
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- If you are looking for assistance, you may be able to find a list of 
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- volunteer staff on '/stats p' (shows only on-call staff) or by joining 
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- #freenode and using the '/who freenode/staff/*' command. You may message
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- any of us at any time. Please note that freenode predominantly provides 
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- assistance via private message, and while we have a network channel the 
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- primary venue for support requests is via private message to a member 
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- of the volunteer staff team.
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	-  
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- From time to time, volunteer staff may send server-wide notices relating to
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- the project, or the communities that we host. The majority of such notices
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- will be sent as wallops, and you can '/mode <yournick> +w' to ensure that you
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- do not miss them. Important messages relating to the freenode project, including
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- notices of upcoming maintenance and other scheduled downtime will be issued as
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- global notices.
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	-  
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- Representing an on-topic project? Don't forget to register, more information
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- can be found on the https://freenode.net website under "Group Registration".
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	-  
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- Thank you also to our server sponsors for the sustained support in keeping the
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- network going for close to two decades.
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	-  
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- Thank you to all of our attendees, sponsors, speakers, exhibitors, helpers,
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- and everyone else who made this year's freenode #live conference amazing.
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- https://freenode.net/news/live-2018
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	-  
2019-12-17 18:05:00	--	- Thank you for using freenode!
